# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Model_Results_2026-06-11/.gitignore
#
# Push scope: 1:1 models only. The 1:10 results/SQL and the King-Zeng
# deployment artifacts are kept SEPARATE (local, not pushed).
#
# The repo-ROOT .gitignore is aggressive (blocks *.csv, *.joblib, *.parquet,
# **/results/ for PHI safety). We re-include ONLY the PHI-free 1:1 result files.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1) Re-include ONLY the 1:1 results tree (root excludes **/results/).
#    1:10 result dirs (*_1to10/) are NOT re-included -> they stay separate.
!**/results/
!**/results/*_1to1/
!**/results/*_1to1/**

# 2) Big trained models stay out (regeneratable, >100 MB) even inside 1:1 results.
#    (tiny platt_calib_*.joblib calibrators are kept — they don't match this.)
model_*.joblib

# 3) 1:10 kept SEPARATE — cohort SQL, launcher/result dirs, and the 1:10 notes excluded from the 1:1 push.
*_1to10.sql
*_1to10/
CALIBRATION_NOTES_1to10.md

# 4) King-Zeng prior-correction artifacts are a deployment concern (parked) and
#    appear inconsistently across cancers — exclude so all result dirs are uniform.
kingzeng_*

# 5) Stale / not-needed-to-run files (excluded from the push):
# - _queue_after_breast.sh: VM queue-orchestration script (hardcoded paths, colon dirs)
# - Holdout.sql: unused legacy; the code reads heldout_test_<gap>mo.sql
_queue_after_breast.sh
Holdout.sql
# - lung standalone analysis one-offs (not imported by the core run path; not needed to run)
recalibrate_holdout.py
recalibrate_kingzeng.py
realworld_eval.py
final_realworld.py
per_band_calib.py
per_model_ci.py
plot_full.py
feat_importance.py
fe_check.py

# 6) Training scratch / telemetry under pipeline_code/.
catboost_info/
**/fe_work_*/
**/raw_*/

# Patient-level prediction parquets under metaclassifier/ stay IGNORED by the
# root rule (*.parquet) on purpose — patient GUIDs. Delivered via GCS (see README).
